# Python programming guidlines

## Logging
- Avoid emojis in log messages.
- Prefer log statements using loggers than print statements.
- Avoid f-strings in logger statements, use proper value place holders instead.

## Type annotation
- Apply type annotations on all function parameters and return types.
- Apply type annotations to local variables.

## Comments
- Avoid emojis in comments.
- Generate comments for functions and methods with the following bullitins: Summary, Parameters and Return value. No need to generate comments about Parameters if the function only takes in ```self```.
- Provide concise explanation to each parameter.

## Error handling
- Only apply try-catch statements when the task in the program do not assign variables that other block of code depends on.

## PyQt and PyQt5
- Ensure compatibility with PyQt6.